---
// Typography Showcase Component for Design System
// Demonstrates font hierarchy, theme-aware text styles, and typography patterns
---

<div class="typography-showcase space-y-16">
  <!-- Font Family Overview -->
  <section>
    <h3 class="text-2xl wireframe-heading mb-6">Wireframe Font System</h3>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      <!-- Short Stack (Primary) -->
      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <h4 class="text-lg wireframe-heading mb-3">
          Short Stack
        </h4>
        <p class="wireframe-text mb-4">
          Primary wireframe font with authentic hand-drawn character. Creates the sketchy, 
          casual feel essential for wireframe aesthetics.
        </p>
        <div class="text-sm theme-card-text opacity-75">Primary wireframe font</div>
      </div>

      <!-- Bricolage Grotesque -->
      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold theme-headline mb-3" style="font-family: 'Bricolage Grotesque Variable', sans-serif;">
          Bricolage Grotesque Variable
        </h4>
        <p class="theme-paragraph mb-4" style="font-family: 'Bricolage Grotesque Variable', sans-serif;">
          Secondary font for clean, modern elements that need more formality within the wireframe design.
        </p>
        <div class="text-sm theme-card-text opacity-75">Secondary display font</div>
      </div>

      <!-- Inter Variable -->
      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold theme-headline mb-3" style="font-family: 'Inter Variable', sans-serif;">
          Inter Variable
        </h4>
        <p class="theme-paragraph mb-4" style="font-family: 'Inter Variable', sans-serif;">
          Fallback font for body text and UI elements requiring high readability and accessibility.
        </p>
        <div class="text-sm theme-card-text opacity-75">Fallback body font</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Wireframe Heading Hierarchy -->
  <section>
    <h3 class="text-2xl wireframe-heading mb-6">Wireframe Heading Hierarchy</h3>
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <!-- H1 Wireframe -->
      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <h1 class="text-6xl wireframe-heading mb-2">H1 Wireframe Heading</h1>
        <code class="text-sm theme-card-text px-2 py-1 rounded" style="background-color: var(--color-theme-quaternary);">text-6xl wireframe-heading</code>
        <p class="text-sm wireframe-text mt-2">Hand-drawn page titles and primary hero headlines</p>
      </div>
      
      <!-- H1 Standard -->
      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <h1 class="text-6xl font-bold theme-headline mb-2">H1 Standard Heading</h1>
        <code class="text-sm theme-card-text px-2 py-1 rounded" style="background-color: var(--color-theme-quaternary);">text-6xl font-bold theme-headline</code>
        <p class="text-sm theme-paragraph mt-2">Standard page titles with fallback fonts</p>
      </div>

      <!-- H2-H6 Wireframe Examples -->
      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <h2 class="text-5xl wireframe-heading mb-2">H2 Wireframe</h2>
        <code class="text-sm theme-card-text px-2 py-1 rounded" style="background-color: var(--color-theme-quaternary);">text-5xl wireframe-heading</code>
        <p class="text-sm wireframe-text mt-2">Hand-drawn section headers</p>
      </div>

      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <h3 class="text-4xl wireframe-heading mb-2">H3 Wireframe</h3>
        <code class="text-sm theme-card-text px-2 py-1 rounded" style="background-color: var(--color-theme-quaternary);">text-4xl wireframe-heading</code>
        <p class="text-sm wireframe-text mt-2">Sketchy subsection headers</p>
      </div>

      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <h4 class="text-3xl wireframe-heading mb-2">H4 Wireframe</h4>
        <code class="text-sm theme-card-text px-2 py-1 rounded" style="background-color: var(--color-theme-quaternary);">text-3xl wireframe-heading</code>
        <p class="text-sm wireframe-text mt-2">Hand-drawn card titles</p>
      </div>

      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <h5 class="text-2xl wireframe-heading mb-2">H5 Wireframe</h5>
        <code class="text-sm theme-card-text px-2 py-1 rounded" style="background-color: var(--color-theme-quaternary);">text-2xl wireframe-heading</code>
        <p class="text-sm wireframe-text mt-2">Minor sketched headers</p>
      </div>

      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <h6 class="text-xl wireframe-heading mb-2">H6 Wireframe</h6>
        <code class="text-sm theme-card-text px-2 py-1 rounded" style="background-color: var(--color-theme-quaternary);">text-xl wireframe-heading</code>
        <p class="text-sm wireframe-text mt-2">Small wireframe headers</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Wireframe Text Variations -->
  <section>
    <h3 class="text-2xl wireframe-heading mb-6">Wireframe Text Variations</h3>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <!-- Paragraph Styles -->
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
          <h4 class="text-lg wireframe-heading mb-4">Wireframe Large Text</h4>
          <p class="text-lg wireframe-text mb-3 leading-relaxed">
            This is large wireframe text with hand-drawn styling. Perfect for introductory 
            sections and content that needs emphasis while maintaining the sketchy aesthetic.
          </p>
          <code class="text-sm theme-card-text px-2 py-1 rounded" style="background-color: var(--color-theme-quaternary);">text-lg wireframe-text leading-relaxed</code>
        </div>

        <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
          <p class="text-base wireframe-text mb-3 leading-normal">
            This is standard wireframe body text with hand-drawn character. Used for most content 
            in the wireframe design system, maintaining readability with authentic sketchy styling.
          </p>
          <code class="text-sm theme-card-text px-2 py-1 rounded" style="background-color: var(--color-theme-quaternary);">text-base wireframe-text leading-normal</code>
        </div>

        <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
          <p class="text-sm wireframe-text mb-3">
            This is small wireframe text maintaining the hand-drawn aesthetic. Ideal for captions, 
            annotations, and secondary information within the wireframe design system.
          </p>
          <code class="text-sm theme-card-text px-2 py-1 rounded" style="background-color: var(--color-theme-quaternary);">text-sm wireframe-text</code>
        </div>

        <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
          <p class="text-xs wireframe-text opacity-75 mb-3">
            This is extra small wireframe text with reduced opacity. Used for fine details, 
            timestamps, and minimal supporting information in the wireframe system.
          </p>
          <code class="text-sm theme-card-text px-2 py-1 rounded" style="background-color: var(--color-theme-quaternary);">text-xs wireframe-text opacity-75</code>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Wireframe Special Styles -->
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
          <h4 class="text-lg wireframe-heading mb-4">Wireframe Special Styles</h4>
          
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <p class="theme-link wireframe-text">Wireframe link text with theme colors</p>
            <p class="theme-highlight wireframe-text font-medium">Highlighted wireframe text</p>
            <p class="text-base wireframe-text font-bold">Bold wireframe text</p>
            <p class="text-base wireframe-text italic">Italic wireframe text</p>
            <p class="text-base wireframe-text underline">Underlined wireframe text</p>
            <p class="text-base wireframe-text line-through opacity-60">Struck-through wireframe text</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Comparison with Standard Styles -->
        <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
          <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold theme-headline mb-4">Standard Special Styles</h4>
          
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <p class="theme-link">Standard link text using theme-link color</p>
            <p class="theme-highlight font-medium">Standard highlighted text with theme-highlight</p>
            <p class="text-base theme-paragraph font-bold">Standard bold paragraph text</p>
            <p class="text-base theme-paragraph italic">Standard italic paragraph text</p>
            <p class="text-base theme-paragraph underline">Standard underlined text</p>
            <p class="text-base theme-paragraph line-through opacity-60">Standard struck-through text</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
          <h4 class="text-lg wireframe-heading mb-4">Code & Monospace</h4>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <p class="wireframe-text">Inline code: <code class="px-2 py-1 rounded font-mono text-sm" style="background-color: var(--color-theme-quaternary); color: var(--color-theme-card-text);">const hello = 'world'</code></p>
            <pre class="p-4 rounded font-mono text-sm overflow-x-auto theme-card-text" style="background-color: var(--color-theme-quaternary); border: 1px solid; border-color: var(--color-theme-stroke);"><code>{`// Code block example
function greet(name) {
  return \`Hello, \${name}!\`;
}`}</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Wireframe Font Weights & Styles -->
  <section>
    <h3 class="text-2xl wireframe-heading mb-6">Wireframe Font Weights & Styles</h3>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <h4 class="wireframe-heading mb-4">Wireframe Font Weights</h4>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <p class="font-light wireframe-text">Light (300) - Wireframe</p>
          <p class="font-normal wireframe-text">Normal (400) - Wireframe</p>
          <p class="font-medium wireframe-text">Medium (500) - Wireframe</p>
          <p class="font-semibold wireframe-text">Semi Bold (600) - Wireframe</p>
          <p class="font-bold wireframe-text">Bold (700) - Wireframe</p>
        </div>
        <p class="text-xs wireframe-text opacity-75 mt-3">Note: Short Stack font has limited weight variations</p>
      </div>

      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <h4 class="wireframe-heading mb-4">Wireframe Text Decorations</h4>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <p class="underline wireframe-text">Underlined wireframe text</p>
          <p class="overline wireframe-text">Overlined wireframe text</p>
          <p class="line-through wireframe-text">Line-through wireframe text</p>
          <p class="no-underline theme-link wireframe-text">Wireframe link without underline</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <h4 class="wireframe-heading mb-4">Wireframe Text Transforms</h4>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <p class="uppercase wireframe-text">UPPERCASE WIREFRAME TEXT</p>
          <p class="lowercase wireframe-text">LOWERCASE WIREFRAME TEXT</p>
          <p class="capitalize wireframe-text">capitalize each wireframe word</p>
          <p class="normal-case wireframe-text">Normal Case Wireframe</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Wireframe Line Heights & Letter Spacing -->
  <section>
    <h3 class="text-2xl wireframe-heading mb-6">Wireframe Line Heights & Letter Spacing</h3>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <h4 class="wireframe-heading mb-4">Wireframe Line Heights</h4>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm theme-card-text mb-1">Tight (leading-tight)</p>
            <p class="leading-tight wireframe-text">
              This wireframe paragraph has tight line height. Hand-drawn text with compact spacing 
              for dense wireframe layouts and annotations.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm theme-card-text mb-1">Normal (leading-normal)</p>
            <p class="leading-normal wireframe-text">
              This wireframe paragraph has normal line height. Standard spacing for most wireframe 
              content that maintains readability while preserving the sketchy aesthetic.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm theme-card-text mb-1">Relaxed (leading-relaxed)</p>
            <p class="leading-relaxed wireframe-text">
              This wireframe paragraph has relaxed line height. Generous spacing for important 
              wireframe descriptions that need extra emphasis and breathing room.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <h4 class="wireframe-heading mb-4">Wireframe Letter Spacing</h4>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm theme-card-text mb-1">Tight (tracking-tight)</p>
            <p class="tracking-tight wireframe-text">Tight letter spacing for compact wireframe layouts.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm theme-card-text mb-1">Normal (tracking-normal)</p>
            <p class="tracking-normal wireframe-text">Normal letter spacing for wireframe readability.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm theme-card-text mb-1">Wide (tracking-wide)</p>
            <p class="tracking-wide wireframe-text">Wide letter spacing for wireframe emphasis.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm theme-card-text mb-1">Wider (tracking-wider)</p>
            <p class="tracking-wider wireframe-text uppercase">PERFECT FOR WIREFRAME HEADINGS</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Monochrome Theme Colors -->
  <section>
    <h3 class="text-2xl wireframe-heading mb-6">Monochrome Theme-Aware Colors</h3>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <h4 class="wireframe-heading font-semibold mb-2">Wireframe Headline</h4>
        <p class="text-sm theme-card-text opacity-75">wireframe-heading</p>
        <p class="text-xs theme-card-text mt-2">Hand-drawn headings with Short Stack</p>
      </div>

      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <p class="wireframe-text font-medium mb-2">Wireframe Text</p>
        <p class="text-sm theme-card-text opacity-75">wireframe-text</p>
        <p class="text-xs theme-card-text mt-2">Hand-drawn body text with sketchy feel</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <h4 class="theme-headline font-semibold mb-2">Standard Headline</h4>
        <p class="text-sm theme-card-text opacity-75">theme-headline</p>
        <p class="text-xs theme-card-text mt-2">Clean headings with fallback fonts</p>
      </div>

      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <h4 class="theme-sub-headline font-semibold mb-2">Sub Headline</h4>
        <p class="text-sm theme-card-text opacity-75">theme-sub-headline</p>
        <p class="text-xs theme-card-text mt-2">Secondary headings and subtitles</p>
      </div>

      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <p class="theme-paragraph font-medium mb-2">Standard Paragraph</p>
        <p class="text-sm theme-card-text opacity-75">theme-paragraph</p>
        <p class="text-xs theme-card-text mt-2">Clean body content and descriptions</p>
      </div>

      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <p class="theme-link font-medium mb-2">Link Color</p>
        <p class="text-sm theme-card-text opacity-75">theme-link</p>
        <p class="text-xs theme-card-text mt-2">Interactive links and CTAs</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Wireframe Usage Examples -->
  <section>
    <h3 class="text-2xl wireframe-heading mb-6">Wireframe Usage Examples</h3>
    <div class="space-y-8">
      <!-- Wireframe Blog Post Preview -->
      <div class="wireframe-box p-8 doodle">
        <h4 class="text-lg wireframe-heading mb-6">Wireframe Blog Post Layout</h4>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-3xl wireframe-heading leading-tight">
            Wireframe Design Principles: Best Practices for 2025
          </h2>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-sm theme-card-text">
            <span>By Wireframe Designer</span>
            <span>•</span>
            <time>March 15, 2024</time>
            <span>•</span>
            <span>5 min read</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-lg wireframe-text leading-relaxed">
            Explore the essential principles of effective wireframe design using hand-drawn 
            aesthetics and monochrome palettes for authentic UX prototyping.
          </p>
          <a href="#" class="theme-link wireframe-text hover:underline font-medium">Read wireframe article →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Wireframe Product Card -->
      <div class="wireframe-box p-8 doodle">
        <h4 class="text-lg wireframe-heading mb-6">Wireframe Product Card Layout</h4>
        <div class="max-w-sm">
          <div class="h-48 rounded-lg mb-4 flex items-center justify-center wireframe-section doodle">
            <span class="wireframe-text">Wireframe Product Image</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl wireframe-heading mb-2">Wireframe Design Kit</h3>
          <p class="wireframe-text mb-4 leading-normal">
            A comprehensive wireframe template kit with hand-drawn components and monochrome styling.
          </p>
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <span class="text-2xl font-bold theme-highlight">$29</span>
            <button class="px-4 py-2 rounded theme-button-primary doodle">Add to Cart</button>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs wireframe-text opacity-75 mt-2">DoodleCSS included</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Wireframe Feature Section -->
      <div class="wireframe-box p-8 doodle">
        <h4 class="text-lg wireframe-heading mb-6">Wireframe Feature Section Layout</h4>
        <div class="text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          <h2 class="text-4xl wireframe-heading mb-4">
            Built for Wireframing
          </h2>
          <p class="text-xl wireframe-text mb-8 leading-relaxed">
            Every component is optimized for authentic hand-drawn wireframe aesthetics
          </p>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 text-left">
            <div class="wireframe-section p-4 doodle">
              <h3 class="text-lg wireframe-heading mb-2">Hand-Drawn Style</h3>
              <p class="wireframe-text text-sm">Short Stack font creates authentic sketchy appearance</p>
            </div>
            <div class="wireframe-section p-4 doodle">
              <h3 class="text-lg wireframe-heading mb-2">Monochrome</h3>
              <p class="wireframe-text text-sm">8 grayscale palettes maintain wireframe consistency</p>
            </div>
            <div class="wireframe-section p-4 doodle">
              <h3 class="text-lg wireframe-heading mb-2">DoodleCSS</h3>
              <p class="wireframe-text text-sm">Enhanced borders and styling for sketch effects</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Wireframe Typography Best Practices -->
  <section>
    <h3 class="text-2xl wireframe-heading mb-6">Wireframe Typography Best Practices</h3>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <h4 class="text-lg wireframe-heading mb-4">✅ Wireframe Do's</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-3 wireframe-text">
          <li>• Use wireframe classes for authentic hand-drawn feel</li>
          <li>• Apply Short Stack font for primary wireframe elements</li>
          <li>• Maintain monochrome color palette consistency</li>
          <li>• Use DoodleCSS classes for enhanced borders</li>
          <li>• Keep appropriate contrast for accessibility</li>
          <li>• Mix wireframe and standard fonts thoughtfully</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="wireframe-box p-6 doodle">
        <h4 class="text-lg wireframe-heading mb-4">❌ Wireframe Don'ts</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-3 wireframe-text">
          <li>• Don't use bright colors in wireframe designs</li>
          <li>• Don't mix too many font families inconsistently</li>
          <li>• Don't ignore the hand-drawn aesthetic guidelines</li>
          <li>• Don't make wireframe text too small to read</li>
          <li>• Don't overuse decorative elements</li>
          <li>• Don't break the monochrome color system</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

<style>
  .typography-showcase {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
  }
  
  /* Ensure wireframe elements use Short Stack font */
  .typography-showcase .wireframe-heading,
  .typography-showcase .wireframe-text {
    font-family: 'Short Stack', var(--font-sans);
  }

  /* Ensure proper spacing for typography examples */
  .typography-showcase code {
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, "SF Mono", Consolas, "Liberation Mono", Menlo, monospace;
  }

  /* Custom styling for better visual separation */
  .typography-showcase section {
    scroll-margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  /* Enhanced code block styling */
  .typography-showcase pre {
    background-color: var(--color-theme-quaternary);
    border: 1px solid;
    border-color: var(--color-theme-stroke);
    opacity: 0.1;
  }

  .typography-showcase code {
    background-color: var(--color-theme-quaternary);
    color: var(--color-theme-card-text);
  }
</style>